{#
  Favicon template driven by a single `variant` string (e.g. "default",
  "dev", "test", ...) that identifies which kind of StrictDoc instance is
  serving this favicon. There is no CSS/browser feature that can express
  "which process served this file" — it has to be baked into the SVG
  bytes themselves. At process start (server startup or a documentation
  export), StrictDoc resolves the favicon variant once via
  ProjectConfig.get_favicon_variant() (strictdoc/core/project_config.py),
  renders the SVG once, and writes it to _static/favicon.svg via
  HTMLGenerator.export_assets() (strictdoc/export/html/html_generator.py).
  Every later browser request just serves that already-rendered file —
  not read live per HTTP request.

  This template only renders for the "default" variant when no custom
  favicon is configured. If ProjectConfig.favicon_path is set, "default"
  serves that file as-is instead — see
  ProjectConfig.get_custom_favicon_path() and
  developer/tasks/20260708_favicon_vars/task_custom_favicon.md. "dev" and
  "test" always render this template, ignoring favicon_path.

  Each variant defines its own light_color/dark_color pair used by the
  @media (prefers-color-scheme) rules below, so prefers-color-scheme
  keeps working independently for every variant. A variant may also add
  markup of its own (see the extra_element block).

  data-testid="{variant}-favicon" on the root <svg> has no runtime effect
  (a favicon is never inserted into a page's DOM) — it exists only so
  tests/unit/strictdoc/export/html/test_favicon.py can assert which
  variant a given render produced without hardcoding colors.

  See developer/design/favicon/favicon.md and
  developer/tasks/20260708_favicon_vars/task.md for the full
  rationale.
#}
{% set variant = variant | default("default") %}

{% if variant == "dev" %}
  {% set light_color = "#000" %}
  {% set dark_color = "#fff" %}
{% elif variant == "test" %}
  {% set light_color = "#000" %}
  {% set dark_color = "#fff" %}
{% else %}
  {% set light_color = "#000" %}
  {% set dark_color = "#fff" %}
{% endif %}

<svg
  data-testid="{{ variant }}-favicon"
  viewBox="0 0 100 100"
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <style>
    .line {
      fill: none;
      stroke-width: 6;
      stroke: #808080;
    }
    .node {
      fill: #808080;
      stroke: none;
    }

    @media (prefers-color-scheme: light) {
      .line { stroke: {{ light_color }}; }
      .node { fill: {{ light_color }}; }
    }
    @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
      .line { stroke: {{ dark_color }}; }
      .node { fill: {{ dark_color }}; }
    }
  </style>

  <path
    class="line"
    d="M 76,35 50,20 24,35 76,65 50,80 24,65"/>

  <circle id="sdoc_n_7" class="node" cx="24" cy="65" r="9.0"/>
  <circle id="sdoc_n_6" class="node" cx="50" cy="80" r="9.0"/>
  <circle id="sdoc_n_5" class="node" cx="76" cy="65" r="9.0"/>
  <circle id="sdoc_n_4" class="node" cx="50" cy="50" r="9.0"/>
  <circle id="sdoc_n_3" class="node" cx="24" cy="35" r="9.0"/>
  <circle id="sdoc_n_2" class="node" cx="50" cy="20" r="9.0"/>
  <circle id="sdoc_n_1" class="node" cx="76" cy="35" r="9.0"/>

  {# Extra per-variant markup goes here, e.g.: #}
  {# {% if variant == "dev" %}<circle cx="88" cy="12" r="8.0"/>{% endif %} #}
</svg>
